<DOC><DOCNO> AP900222-0055 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-22-90 0646EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Philippines-American     02-22 0154</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Philippines-American,0157</SECOND><HEAD>American, Two Filipinos Killed in Ambush</HEAD><DATELINE>CEBU CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Gunmen ambushed a jeep in thecentral Philippines, killing an American, his Filipino wife andfather-in-law, the military and U.S. officials said today.   A report by the Philippine Constabulary said the killings tookplace Wednesday along a highway on Bohol island, 400 milessoutheast of Manila. The American was identified as John RobertMitchell, 42, of Fairbanks, Alaska.   U.S. Consul Franklin Huddle confirmed the American victim'sidentity, but said he did not know what Mitchell did in thePhilippines or how long he has been in the country.   The constabulary report said assailants fled after firing M-16sand rifles at the jeep that Mitchell drove. Mitchell was fatallyshot, as was his wife, Marilou Chatoo, 24, and her father, Silvino.   The military said it was investigating whether the attack wascarried out by Communist rebels, who operate in the area.</TEXT></DOC>